stellar C/O. This shows that while the solids\nwill tend to be oxygen rich, Hot Jupiters can have super-stellar C/O if a\ncarbon excess can be maintained by some chemical processing of the dust grains.\nWhether the carbon and oxygen content of the atmosphere was accreted primarily\nby gas or solid accretion is heavily dependent on the mass of the atmosphere\nand where in the disk the growing planet accreted.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 Jan 2019 14:54:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-17"}
